1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Now you just pretend you hadn't talked to me any before, and you tell me about the government moving you up here.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Well, now, I don't remember the day or the month or nothing like that, you understand?

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:19,000
But I know they come one evening, and I just was fixing to quit working in my garden.

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:27,000
And he comes and he says, well, says, is this Miss Davis?

5
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
And I said, that's what they called me.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Other words ain't new, I said, yes.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:39,000
He says, well, says, I'm taking pictures around.

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Says the government's going to take over everything, and Jamesworth's going to have to move out.

9
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,000
I said, all this many years? I said, you talk crazy.

10
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:54,000
And he lay, he says, no.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Says, I'm here just to tell you, says, friendly talk.

12
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:08,000
And he says, then my chicken was all out, and it was late in the evening, you know.

13
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
I told him, I says, well, you'll have to excuse me.

14
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:16,000
I got to put my chicken in the chicken yard.

15
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
He says, that's just what I want you to do.

16
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
Well, there was a shark fellow with him, you know.

17
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:26,000
But he didn't ever tell me who he was, you understand?

18
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
And I went to put my chickens in the chicken yard and fed them.

19
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:36,000
And I had on my old bonnet and shirt where I'd been working, you know.

20
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,000
And I throwed the corn out.

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:44,000
And I noticed this shark fellow walked up close to him and said something or another.

22
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:50,000
And he said, well, you've got a pretty bunch of chickens, says, do they lay?

23
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
I says, yes.

24
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:57,000
I says, sometimes I pick up nine eggs a day, and sometimes I don't.

25
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:01,000
He says, well, this surely is a pretty place.

26
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Well, I didn't know this shark man walked up to him and took my picture

27
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,000
just as I went to throw some corn out to him, you know.

